Title: Core Arguments of Published Research
Details: 2. be able to identify and explain the core arguments of published research on the topic of study, and be able to interpret and report on the findings outlined in the data and articles studied;

Analyze the following learning outcome and provide confidence scores for how well it aligns with each BYU Aim:

Title: Key Theories and Analyses
Details: General Learning Outcomes for German 497 1. understand and be able to describe keytheories and analyses proposed to account for topics and phenomena related to the relevant field of study investigated in the course, e.g., for the acquisition of new sounds in a second language (L2), contrastive analysis, markedness differential hypothesis, as well as new theories such as Flege's SLM and Best's PAM;

Analyze the following learning outcome and provide confidence scores for how well it aligns with each BYU Aim:

Title: Explaining Individual Beliefs and Views
Details: 3. be able to describe and explain our individual beliefs and views on a given topic related to Germanic linguistics discussed in class and be able to reassess our views and beliefs by weighing the evidence presented in published research, defininghow these findings support or contradict our views;

Analyze the following learning outcome and provide confidence scores for how well it aligns with each BYU Aim:

Title: Identifying Relevant Topics in Germanic Linguistics
Details: 4. be able to identify atopic of relevance in Germanic linguistics relating to the course topic, and carry out research on the topic by identifyingand understandingthe key articles on that topic and synthesise the findings in a clearly communicated paper and presentation to othersin which the student's points are effectively and logically argued;

Analyze the following learning outcome and provide confidence scores for how well it aligns with each BYU Aim:

Title: Seeking out Sources
Details: 5. be able to seek out sources on topics in Germanic linguistics and/or second language acquisition;

Analyze the following learning outcome and provide confidence scores for how well it aligns with each BYU Aim:

Title: Critical Reading, Summarizing, and Communicating
Details: 6. be able to critically read, summarise and clearly communicate the core arguments and findings of published research on Germanic linguistics topics related to the course theme by means of an annotated bibliography, paper overview, final paper and presentation;
